From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 14:20:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Route CoFunc TDX VMCALL leaves to userspace for 5.19

The 5.19 CoFunc host patch adds split-container VM/vCPU plumbing and marks
CoFunc idle VCPUs when a userspace-routed TDX VMCALL is already in progress,
but it does not route the CoFunc TDX leaves themselves to userspace.

Without these cases, a standard TDG.VP.VMCALL with R10=0 and R11=0x10011
falls into handle_tdvmcall()'s default case and returns
TDG_VP_VMCALL_INVALID_OPERAND before QEMU can run its CoFunc handler.
---
 arch/x86/kvm/vmx/tdx.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/tdx.c b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/tdx.c
index 12dc3b963..5d1a5e51c 100644
--- a/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/tdx.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/vmx/tdx.c
@@ -1829,10 +1829,17 @@ static int handle_tdvmcall(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu)
 	case TDG_VP_VMCALL_SETUP_EVENT_NOTIFY_INTERRUPT:
 		r = tdx_setup_event_notify_interrupt(vcpu);
 		break;
 	case TDG_VP_VMCALL_GET_QUOTE:
 		r = tdx_get_quote(vcpu);
 		break;
+	case KVM_HC_TDX_SC_VCPU_IDLE:
+	case KVM_HC_TDX_SC_REQUEST:
+		/*
+		 * CoFunc TDX split-container requests are handled by QEMU.
+		 */
+		r = tdx_vp_vmcall_to_user(vcpu);
+		break;
 	default:
 		tdvmcall_set_return_code(vcpu, TDG_VP_VMCALL_INVALID_OPERAND);
 		r = 1;
 		break;
